cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.DC 

This paper discusses a congestion avoidance scheme for ATM networks, which falls under the category of network protocols and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the Resource Management (RM) cell format, which is related to security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The scheme also involves rate feedback and input rate as a congestion metric, which are related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. The paper also discusses fair operation and high utilization, which are related to communication and distributed systems, making cs.COMM (Computer Communication and Networks) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the scheme, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a less likely but still possible category.
